ALFRED JAMES NEWTON , Bart. Alderman, LORD MAYOR of the City of London; the Hon. Sir WILLIAM GRANTHAM, Knt., one of the Judges of Her Majesty's High Court; Sir REGINALD HANSON, Bart., M.P., LL.D., F.S.A., Sir GEORGE F. FAUDEL PHILLIPS, Bart., G.C.I.E., Aldermen of the said City; Sir FORREST FULTON, Knt., Q.C., Recorder of the said City; Sir JOSEPH COCKFIELD DIMSDALE, Knt.;
JOHN POUND , Esq.; JOHN CHARLES BELL, Esq,. other of the Aldermen of the said City; and FREDERICK ALBERT BOSANQUET, Q.C., Common Serjeant of the said City; Her Majesty's Justices of Oyer and Terminer and General Gaol Delivery, holden for the said City, and Judges of the Central Criminal Court.

MESSRS. HORACE AVORY, MUIR, and JAY 
